{"name": "rdpermute", "metadata": {"name": "rdpermute", "version": "0.1.0", "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["rdrobust", "stata-setup", "jupyter-console", "pytest"], "summary": "Perform permutation test proposed by Ganong and J\u00e4ger (2018) https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/full/10.1080/01621459.2017.1328356", "upload_time": 1735650197}, "documentation": ["# rdpermute\n\nPython package to perform the regression kink design (RKD) permutation test proposed by [Ganong and J\u00e4ger (2018)](https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/full/10.1080/01621459.2017.1328356).\n\nThis package is inspired by the Stata package of the same name [`rdpermute`](https://github.com/ganong-noel/rdpermute) relying heavily on the excellent [`rdrobust`](https://github.com/rdpackages/rdrobust). Contrary to the Stata package [`rdpermute`](https://github.com/ganong-noel/rdpermute), this package implements confidence intervals based on randomization inference following the algorithm proposed by [Ganong and J\u00e4ger (2018)](https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/full/10.1080/01621459.2017.1328356) (see Appendix C).  It also uses Python's [`multiprocessing`](https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html) resulting in better performance compared to the Stata package."], "modules": [{"name": "rdpermute", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "rdpermute.rdpermute", "xref": {"fqname": "rdpermute.rdpermute.rdpermute", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "rdpermute.enums", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "rdpermute.enums.RegressionType", "bases": ["enum.Enum"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "rdpermute.enums.RegressionType.RDD", "type": null, "documentation": ["regression discontinuity design: discontinuity in level"]}, {"name": "rdpermute.enums.RegressionType.RKD", "type": null, "documentation": ["regression kink design: discontinuity in first derivative"]}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "rdpermute.enums.PolynomialDegree", "bases": ["enum.Enum"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "rdpermute.enums.PolynomialDegree.linear", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rdpermute.enums.PolynomialDegree.quad", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rdpermute.enums.PolynomialDegree.cubic", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "rdpermute.enums.Kernel", "bases": ["enum.Enum"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "rdpermute.enums.Kernel.uniform", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rdpermute.enums.Kernel.triangular", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rdpermute.enums.Kernel.epanechnikov", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "rdpermute.enums.BandwidthSelector", "bases": ["enum.Enum"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "rdpermute.enums.BandwidthSelector.mse", "type": null, "documentation": ["mean squared error (MSE)-optimal bandwidth selector"]}, {"name": "rdpermute.enums.BandwidthSelector.cer", "type": null, "documentation": ["coverage error rate (CER)-optimal bandwidth selector"]}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "rdpermute.enums.BandwidthSelectorFunction", "bases": ["enum.Enum"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "rdpermute.enums.BandwidthSelectorFunction.rd", "type": null, "documentation": ["one common bandwidth"]}, {"name": "rdpermute.enums.BandwidthSelectorFunction.two", "type": null, "documentation": ["two different bandwidths (below and above the cutoff)"]}, {"name": "rdpermute.enums.BandwidthSelectorFunction.sum", "type": null, "documentation": ["one common bandwidth for the sum of regression estimates (as opp